Implemented and pushed the follow-up to PR [#10](https://github.com/tcrypt25519/zkpow/pull/10).

Production batch loading now skips full `HeaderRecord` construction. It queries only the witness fields needed for proving: `version`, `merkle_root`, `timestamp`, `nonce`, and `median_time_past`, then fills `Vec<NewHeader>` and `Vec<BlockTimestamp>` directly. Full-header loading stays available for DB-backed state reconstruction and tests.

Validation passed: `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo test -p zkpow-host --lib`, `cargo test -p zkpow-core --lib`, one-header execute-only smoke, and `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings`.

Commit: `18f0ed3 refactor: load host batch witnesses directly`. GitHub still reports no checks on PR #10.

